node.text: “Fulfillment comes not from someplace far away, but from learning to appreciate everything around me, as if I’m seeing it for the very first time.” @ChelseaKauai used the #OsmoAction to document a day of capturing the simple and extraordinary things that sparked her imagination close to home.
There are a couple of #DJI presents hiding in this room full of holiday decorations. Can you find them all?

“A morning in Hawaii. The sound of the ocean. Hot bullet coffee. Exploring new places. Fresh dew on the grass. Dirty bare feet. That pinch of adrenaline.” We paired creator and athlete @caleyvanular with the #OsmoAction to capture her perfect day. Feelings of wanderlust all around. #seeyourselfinaction @roam

“I’ve kept an #OsmoAction in my pocket all month, capturing little clips along the way. It’s been the perfect tool to capture authentic moments as they happen, allowing me to craft those moments into a story. Into my story.” We paired photographer @tedhesser with the #OsmoAction to tell a narrative about his journey to becoming a fulltime creative. #seeyourselfinaction @roam

Climber, skier, and Academy Award-winning filmmaker @jimmychin has explored some of the most breathtaking places on earth. As a professional cinematographer and world traveler, it’s essential for him to have equipment that’s compact, durable, and capable of delivering epic results. Tools like #DJI’s #OsmoAction camera let Jimmy spend less time worrying about gear, and more time living the action. Click the link in our bio to discover more about Jimmy’s recent trip to #Moab, Utah with the Osmo Action.
—
Directed by: @jimmychin & @dirkcollins 
Produced by: Little Monster Films
Edited by: @rodophoto

This short video was entirely filmed on the #MavicMini with less than four batteries in total. Isn’t it mind blowing that you can achieve this on a drone that costs less than $400 and fits in your pocket?! | Credit: @ferdigrapher

Join the fun by submitting a one-minute video on Instagram! Add the #DJINoPlaceLikeHome hashtag and tag @DJIGlobal and one friend for a chance to win some incredible DJI handheld products! Your footage should show what “home” means to you. Show off your city, neighborhood, or community. Submissions are open starting December 15, 2019 and will close on January 15, 2020. T&C apply, read more at http://bit.ly/DJI-UGC-TC. @saltyluxe @yusukeokawa @mayadstudios @mayadacademy @lukebakhuizen @thejianhaotan

The Hawaiian islands of Kauai and Oahu are known for their evergreen landscapes, endless pathways, and beaches that are perfect from sunrise to sunset. With the pocket-sized #MavicMini and a touch of imagination, #DJICreator @RabbitFilms showcases that when we dive into Kauai’s nature, the possibilities are limitless.

“BASE jumping is an unforgiving sport both to participate in and to shoot,” says photographer Savannah Cummins @sav.cummins. “There's no second chances and no ‘hey, do that again.’” Savannah learns best by doing so we decided to equip her with the #OsmoAction to capture her first tandem BASE jump. The RockSteady feature saved her shaky hands from distorting any shots and the 8x slow-mo allowed her to rewatch the footage and break down how this BASE jumping thing really works. @roam #SeeYourselfInAction

“I’m a storyteller. I’m obsessed with every part of it, from the epic moments to the smallest details,” says Ryan Robinson @handsomerobinson . As a highliner and creative, Ryan relies on three main things to carry out his vision: location, company, and tools. 
We partnered up with Ryan and equipped him with the perfect companion for his most recent trip to Pedra da Gavea, Brazil, the #OsmoAction. 
Pedra da Gavea offers the perfect location, jutting 3,000+ feet up above the ocean below and with the help of his friends, his story really comes to life. “I’ve always tried my best to take people into my mind and into my eyes so they can feel the heights, the depth, the fear that I’m feeling.” That’s why having the right camera is paramount to making everything come together. 
@roam #seeyourselfinaction

Iceland features some of the most extreme and interesting landscapes on the planet and a multitude of iconic filming locations. Follow along as @johnny_fpv and DJI Creative Director, @ferdigrapher, soar through the skies testing DJI’s Digital FPV System. Enjoy this behind-the-scenes video of jaw-dropping canyons, breathtaking waterfalls, and gorgeous glaciers.

“From Dubai to Bali, I put this camera to the test. From the gimbal like stability without a gimbal, incredible 4K and slow motion footage, front and back facing screens, and lastly, I really tested durability when it survived being dropped at 50km/h with just a minor scratch. Truly impressed by the #OsmoAction.” - Christian LeBlanc @lostleblanc

We recently partnered up with adventure photographer Callum Snape @calsnape to tell a story about his experience returning home to the Canadian Rockies. We equipped him with the #OsmoAction to capture the breathtaking scenes in this meditative video shot entirely on the action camera.

@roam #seeyourselfinaction
Relive The Color Run from the inside! Thanks to @redscopefilms we captured the best moments of the race in Sydney with the #DJI #OsmoAction.

"One side of the world to another. The sky to the sea. Tonga and Belize had to have been two of the wildest experiences of my life. One week I found myself swimming with humpback whales, and the next skydiving into The Blue Hole, a Unesco Heritage site 50km off the coast of Belize." We partnered up with filmmaker, director and aerial cinematographer, Zachary Moxley @downtofilm to take the #OsmoAction through its paces in these polar opposite environments. The Osmo Action is compact and extremely versatile eliminating the need for big camera rigs, yet perfectly capable of capturing the perfect shot in any situation. 
@roam #seeyourselfinaction

The #RoboMasterS1 is the perfect gift for kids or kidults this Christmas. With its powerful capabilities, highly customizable interface, and programming flexibility the RoboMaster S1 is ready for creativity.

When you think of #Munich, Germany, surfing is probably not the first thing that comes to mind. Since its construction in 1972, the Eisbach has been drawing surfers from around the world who brave its freezing waters to catch this never-ending river wave. #DJICreator @saltst visited to capture all the action with #MavicMini.

One of the most iconic cities in South America, #riodejaneiro is an epic visual wonderland. From sparkling beaches along the coastline up into the vibrant green mountains, it’s the perfect location to capture the view from above. #DJICreator Guilherme Coelho from @rabbitfilms uses his #MavicMini to do just that.

Creative and Entrepreneur, Chase Jarvis @chasejarvis took the #DJI #OsmoAction out for a spin last week. "From mud, to water to air, this little beast packs a punch (4K, 8x slow-mo, waterproof, etc). Boggles my mind that we've now got so much horsepower... in a camera that fits in my mouth. Front-facing screen and stabilization are shockingly good - makes me wonder how we lived without em for so long!" #seeyourselfinaction @roam @creativelive
The colors on fall in North America brought to you by @emadrashidi and the #DJI #Mavic2Pro 🍁
Check out how the #DJI #OsmoAction was used inside and outside of cars competing in the D1 GRAND PRIX (@d1gpse) to capture all the excitement of one of the world’s most famous drifting competitions.
You don't need to log thousands of hours in a flight simulator to fly the #DJI #MavicMini, just a few minutes using the DJI Fly app's flight tutorial mode, and you'll be ready to go.
